<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-063-259 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 216 657</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Sept 9 1991 v8 n36 p28(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Expert-system package targets service industry. (Business ResourceSoftware Inc. introduces Business Insight for the ServiceIndustry) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ferranti, Marc.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Business Resource Software (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Business Insight for the Service Industry (Decision supportsoftware) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionDecision Support SystemsSoftware packagesExpert systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Marc FerrantiandM;Business Resource Software Inc. has released a new version of its BusinessInsight expert-system program tuned for users in the service industry.andM;Business Insight for the Service Industry, due next month, is a rule-basedexpert system programmed to help analysts and managers assess and formulatestrategies for service-related companies.andM;The DOS program, like its earlier manufacturing-oriented version -- calledsimply Business Insight -- features a menu-driven interface with pull-downmenus and dialog boxes, said company officials.andM;The program evaluates strategies by comparing answers users give to a seriesof questions about their business to basic rules about the service industry,stored in the program's &quot;knowledge base.&quot;andM;The $495 program is available directly from the Austin, Texas, company, whichcan be reached at (800) 423-1228.andO;</TEXT></DOC>